,Recommended,428950,21197998,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,TreyGamr58,"I was browsing the most absolutely cheapest things on sale on the Lunar New Year Sale and I stumble upon this little thing. I mostly got it because I felt confident about spending for nearly anything after replenishing my steam wallet and that I really dig this kind of deserty wasteland theme.It was alright enough. I haven't played for that long or gotten too far but, from what I've played so far, I'm pretty sure it's good enough for a 99₵ pricetag. It does what it's suppose to do thoroughly and it doesn't hold your hand. You have to really think and be cautious when progressing and to also be aware about all the variables that you have to take care of. I've noticed that most of these other reviewers are saying that they can't get to the 2nd town because ""the game's unfair"" when they probably didn't upgrade their vehicle (repair vehicle if below 60, fuel up, attach 2nd AK turret, and maybe buy some off-road tires) and keep their distance from enemy cars.This game is more complicated than I anticipated and you need to plan out your journey so that you won't be relying only on the RNG. It does not have everything that it should. It should give you the ability to rebind some controls (the controls could take some getting used to), it's sort of luck based, the combat could be better and more built upon, and there's a major lack of toilets here.It's alright, especially for it price, it's not garbage, it is challenging (like how old NES games were challenging), and it may be a good distraction in between of doing things or waiting for a bigger game of yours to get patched.I may have only played around a halfhour but I don't regret this small purchase. Heck, you could probably just get a refund if you don't like it after a few sessions or go for the trading cards and make a profit of the marketplace. I know that I'm gonna keep this one around."
