76561197963164050,Not Recommended,428950,20878213,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,NighT WolF,"It starts good with an instruction of the few basic elements it has, but later on it completly destroys itself with really bad balancing. (You will barely take a scratch from the first boss, but regular enemies can drain your hp within seconds.) There is a lot of wasted potential and it feels like the devs abandoned it when they were halfway through.The items drop randomly, so if you are not really carefully how and when you speed up while driving and keep your distance to enemies, you will have a hard time to survive, because HP-Packs won't drop at all sometimes. Some of the items are not explained, so you have to figure it out on your own, what exactly they do.There are a few upgrades that doesn't make sense, since it would make the game harder. Why should i buy a pistol for my car, when it has an automatic rifle by default? You can beat the entire game with the automatic rifles (for the Car and Char). You won't need anything else.The balancing for the boss battles would really need some improvements and changes. The second boss is probably the hardest, while every other boss is rather too easy. You can even hit them, when they can't hit you and some of them are stationary.Graphics are okay for such a simple game and have some fine details.It could have a few more sounds. You don't even hear your car while driving.But beside all of that you can get fun out of it, when you like games of this kind and if you want a challenge that can be frustrating from time to time. The concept is good, but it has much wasted potential. It's hard to give a yes or no, since you can see some effort the devs put into that game, but it feels in many situations like they haven't finished their job."
76561198024735043,Recommended,428950,23532292,"Posted: 12 June, 2016",all,[E.K.] puzzle,"I love this game, probably too much.  It's hard, short, and occasionally unforgivingly buggy, but it's a complete game and almost elegant in it's minimalism.  For me it really scratches that retro, post-apocalyptic late 80's arcade itch.The concept is super simple, you play a guy driving down a broken road in some post apocalypse wasteland heading for some unstated destination.  Along the way there are towns where you can pay for repairs and buy ammo, fuel, guns etc for you and your car.  In between the towns are bad guys you have to avoid or kill for loot.  Entering each town triggers a fight either with some waves of bad guys or one of 5 scripted bosses that you have to beat before you can do your shopping.  The difficulty is in preserving your armor, conserving your ammo and picking up enough cash along the way.  Oh and avoiding canyons.  Those things can be brutal."
